# QField Sync Data Diagnosis & System Proposals

This document analyzes the synchronized datasets from the QField project located in the `c:\Users\ndebelem.ZINGSERVER1\Desktop\2026\QField` folder, diagnoses the contents, and proposes various systems that can be built using these datasets.

---

## 1. Overview of the Sync Folder

The workspace contains files synchronized from a **QField mobile data collection project** (titled **MyTrees**), which appears to be a community-based reforestation, forest conservation, carbon sequestration, and local livelihood initiative (located in the **Hurungwe** district of Zimbabwe, based on administrative boundary data).

### Core Folder Structure
- **GeoPackage Datasets (`*.gpkg`)**: 27 SQLite-based spatial databases containing tables, fields, and geometries (points, polygons, line tracks) mapping the forestry lifecycle.
- **Media Directories**:
  - `DCIM/` (750 files): Photos captured by field agents (jpg, png, heic formats) documenting tree growth, nurseries, fire damage, training sessions, and grower verification.
  - `audio/` (38 files): Audio notes or field recordings captured during verifications or audits.
- **QGIS Project Files**:
  - `MTT Field_cloud.qgs`: The primary QGIS XML project file defining map styling, layers, and QField synchronization rules.
  - `MTT Field_cloud.qgd`: The associated QGIS sqlite database storing local configurations.
  - `MTT Field_cloud_attachments.zip`: Archive files for the project environment.

---

## 2. GeoPackage Dataset Breakdown

Below is a diagnostic summary of the data tables, row counts, and main attributes within each GeoPackage file:

| File Name | Primary Table | Row Count | Geometry Type | Key Attributes & Focus |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Aftercare.gpkg** | `Aftercare` | 37,921 | Point | grower details, spacing, slashing, pruning, fire guards, survival %, supervisor name. *(Largest spatial layer)* |
| **MeetingsTrainings.gpkg** | `MeetingsTrainings` | 39,581 | Point | meeting type, agenda, attendants list, audio/photos, decisions, minutes, cluster. |
| **Work-Plan.gpkg** | `Work-Plan` | 10,651 | Point | name, role, Monday-to-Friday schedules, field activities, challenges, recommendations. |
| **Nursery Production Verification.gpkg** | `Nursery Production Verification` | 5,790 | Point | nursery name, work rate, growth stage, next visit date, completion level, recommendations. |
| **Planting Update.gpkg** | `Planting Update` | 2,712 | Point | target vs. planted counts, variance, species 1–7 details, grower surname, program type. |
| **Species Distribution.gpkg** | `Species Distribution` | 2,786 | Point | monitor name, specie type, land use location type, date. |
| **FieldVerification.gpkg** | `FieldVerification` | 1,814 | Point | monitor, ward, village, grower name, findings, type, conclusion, decision, field audio. |
| **PlotMapping.gpkg** | `PlotMapping` | 1,757 | MultiPolygon | grower ID, survival rates, trees planted vs. alive, plot size, year established, program type. |
| **SurvivalCount.gpkg** | `SurvivalCount` | 1,457 | Point | trees planted/alive, height classifications (0–50cm, 51–100cm, 101–150cm, 151–200cm) across 11 species. |
| **FireAssessement.gpkg** | `FireAssessement` | 593 | Point | grower, cause of fire, start/end time, slashed status, burnt area size, survival count, comments. |
| **Nursery.gpkg** | `Nursery` | 311 | Point | pocketed/germinated seeds, ready counts for species 1–6, weeding/pruning status, monthly mortalities. |
| **MTT Plot Selection.gpkg** | `MTT Plot Selection` | 288 | Point | grower name, ward, cluster, status (approved/pending). |
| **PlotAssessment.gpkg** | `PlotAssessment` | 264 | MultiPolygon | soil type, land use, width/length, coppices, dominant species, existing biomass, calculated biomass. |
| **Beekeeping.gpkg** | `Beekeeping` | 160 | Point | hive ID, hive type, bee type, colonization status, waxed, mounted, honey quality, quantity. |
| **User Tracks.gpkg** | `User Tracks` | 129 | LineString | field agent name, date, track distance (km), length. *(Used to audit agent patrols)* |
